477
00:37:20,977 --> 00:37:23,977
Because there was something left behind.

478
00:37:27,977 --> 00:37:32,977
That's this black notebook. ➡

479
00:37:32,977 --> 00:37:36,977
This black notebook contains things that our seniors have accumulated ➡

480
00:37:36,977 --> 00:37:40,977
Everything was packed.

481
00:37:40,977 --> 00:37:43,977
Every time you turn the page➡

482
00:37:43,977 --> 00:37:46,977
Voices of seniors thinking about space➡

483
00:37:46,977 --> 00:37:50,977
I felt like I could hear it.

484
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:52,977
I want to fly into space!

485
00:37:52,977 --> 00:37:55,977
Just a few more steps to space!

486
00:37:55,977 --> 00:37:58,977
Deliver it to space! ⚟To space!

487
00:37:58,977 --> 00:38:00,977
⚟To space! (Kanahito) To space!

488
00:38:00,977 --> 00:38:02,977
⚟To space!

489
00:38:02,977 --> 00:38:06,977
We repeated trial and error and finally➡

490
00:38:06,977 --> 00:38:11,977
We were able to complete canned mackerel that met the standards required by JAXA.

491
00:38:11,977 --> 00:38:18,977
Then, in order to receive certification, it was submitted to preservation inspection for one and a half years.

492
00:38:20,977 --> 00:38:25,977
The other day, I received an inspection notification from JAXA➡

493
00:38:25,977 --> 00:38:32,977
As a result, the certification was not denied.

494
00:38:32,977 --> 00:38:42,977
(Students' noise)

495
00:38:42,977 --> 00:38:48,977
The taste had changed during storage...

496
00:38:50,977 --> 00:38:53,977
It was frustrating.

497
00:38:53,977 --> 00:38:55,977
(Suzu) It was sad.

498
00:38:55,977 --> 00:38:59,977
(Kanahito) We wanted to fly it with our own hands.

499
00:39:02,977 --> 00:39:08,977
(Ruka) But I didn't think it would be enough to just send it into space. ➡

500
00:39:08,977 --> 00:39:12,977
I want to deliver delicious food to space. ➡

501
00:39:12,977 --> 00:39:17,977
That's why we've continued to make improvements. ➡

502
00:39:17,977 --> 00:39:21,977
Space mackerel cans➡

503
00:39:21,977 --> 00:39:27,977
We were unable to complete it in our generation.

504
00:39:29,977 --> 00:39:36,977
(Ruka) But I left everything here.

505
00:39:38,977 --> 00:39:43,977
Recipes that failed and quantities that worked ➡

506
00:39:43,977 --> 00:39:48,977
All the days I was disappointed and the days I didn't give up.

507
00:39:52,977 --> 00:39:57,977
So…➡

508
00:39:57,977 --> 00:40:02,977
Our dream is➡

509
00:40:02,977 --> 00:40:06,977
I will leave it to my juniors.

510
00:40:06,977 --> 00:40:11,977
Just like our predecessors did➡

511
00:40:11,977 --> 00:40:17,977
Our role was to connect them to the next one.

512
00:40:19,977 --> 00:40:27,977
From here on... I'll leave it to you!

513
00:40:27,977 --> 00:40:33,977
Your role is to send canned mackerel into space.

514
00:40:36,977 --> 00:40:40,977
With your hands➡

515
00:40:40,977 --> 00:40:43,977
Please connect the Sabakaido to space.

516
00:40:51,977 --> 00:41:11,977
(applause)

517
00:41:11,977 --> 00:41:15,977
(Student) This concludes the inquiry learning presentation.

518
00:41:24,977 --> 00:41:26,977
(Ruka) Teacher.

519
00:41:26,977 --> 00:41:29,977
It was a great presentation.

520
00:41:34,977 --> 00:41:36,977
this .

521
00:41:43,977 --> 00:41:47,977
When I got this shell back➡

522
00:41:47,977 --> 00:41:51,977
I felt like I was moving forward.

523
00:41:51,977 --> 00:41:54,977
Dreams don't disappear.

524
00:41:57,977 --> 00:42:01,977
So thanks to the teacher.

525
00:42:01,977 --> 00:42:03,977
Because the teacher came to me➡

526
00:42:03,977 --> 00:42:09,977
We could think for ourselves.

527
00:42:09,977 --> 00:42:11,977
I was able to move by myself.

528
00:42:11,977 --> 00:42:15,977
I was able to fail on my own.

529
00:42:17,977 --> 00:42:21,977
Even the teacher feels bad about not being able to fly.

530
00:42:21,977 --> 00:42:24,977
I must have experienced it many times.

531
00:42:24,977 --> 00:42:27,977
Always look like you're okay in front of us➡

532
00:42:27,977 --> 00:42:31,977
I asked him to watch over me.

533
00:42:31,977 --> 00:42:36,977
The teacher was just watching over us➡

534
00:42:36,977 --> 00:42:40,977
You might think so➡

535
00:42:40,977 --> 00:42:44,977
I've been looking at you for a long time.

536
00:42:46,977 --> 00:42:50,977
(Ruka) When you are anxious➡

537
00:42:50,977 --> 00:42:53,977
When you don't know what to do➡

538
00:42:53,977 --> 00:42:58,977
Whenever I looked back, the teacher was there.

539
00:43:01,977 --> 00:43:06,977
I have a teacher who believes in me and watches over me.

540
00:43:08,977 --> 00:43:11,977
(Ruka) That's why I've come this far.

541
00:43:16,977 --> 00:43:18,977
(Ruka) Mr. Asano.

542
00:43:21,977 --> 00:43:28,977
For bringing us this far...➡

543
00:43:28,977 --> 00:43:31,977
thank you .

544
00:43:41,977 --> 00:43:43,977
you're welcome .

545
00:43:51,977 --> 00:44:02,977
(applause)

546
00:44:02,977 --> 00:44:08,977
♬～

547
00:44:08,977 --> 00:44:23,977
♬～

548
00:44:23,977 --> 00:44:27,977
I'm back again.

549
00:44:27,977 --> 00:44:30,977
The three years went by so quickly. (Suzu) Na.

550
00:44:30,977 --> 00:44:32,977
But I felt like I finally understood it.

551
00:44:32,977 --> 00:44:34,977
(Suzu/Ruka) Huh? (Nana Uta) Why everyone➡

552
00:44:34,977 --> 00:44:38,977
Could you be that serious? (Suzu) Me too.

553
00:44:38,977 --> 00:44:42,977
What? (Ruka) What is that! Hey.

554
00:44:42,977 --> 00:44:44,977
It's a secret just for us. (Suzu) It's a secret.

555
00:44:44,977 --> 00:44:46,977
What's the secret? It's no big deal anyway.

556
00:44:46,977 --> 00:44:51,977
Ah, that's annoying. (Kanahito) Why, why...stop it.

557
00:44:53,977 --> 00:44:56,977
[Dreams are spinning]

558
00:44:56,977 --> 00:44:58,977
[From light to darkness]

559
00:44:58,977 --> 00:45:01,977
[From darkness to light]

560
00:45:01,977 --> 00:45:05,977
[Repeat Repeat]

561
00:45:07,977 --> 00:45:12,977
[Dreams will never disappear as long as there is someone to embrace them]

562
00:45:12,977 --> 00:45:32,977
♬～

563
00:45:32,977 --> 00:45:34,977
♬～

564
00:45:34,977 --> 00:45:40,977
[This epic dream journey leads to the next one]
